==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Clairaudience
<hw>Clair*au"di*ence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>clair</ets> clear + F. & E. <ets>audience</ets> a hearing. See
<er>Clear</er>.]</ety> <def>Act of hearing, or the ability to hear,
sounds not normally audible; -- usually claimed as a special faculty of
spiritualistic mediums, or the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clairaudient</ent>⟦br⟧
